-bearer&#8221;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<dl>\n<dt>Kingdom<\/dt>\n<dd>Microsynthera<\/dd>\n<dt>Phylum<\/dt>\n<dd>Plasticae<\/dd>\n<dt>Class<\/dt>\n<dd>Occlupanida<\/dd>\n<dt>Order<\/dt>\n<dd>Orthogonidectes<\/dd>\n<dt>Family<\/dt>\n<dd>Toxodentidae<\/dd>\n<dt>Genus<\/dt>\n<dd>Palpatophora<\/dd>\n<dt>Species<\/dt>\n<dd>magnastoma<\/dd>\n<dt>External morphology<\/dt>\n<\/dl>\n<p>Lateral palps. Size 21.5 mm x 26 mm<\/p>\n<div class=\"description\">\n<p>At first glance P. magnastoma could be one of a few very common occlupanid species: <em>P. glyphodorsalis<\/em>, <em>P. utiliformis<\/em>, or <em>P. utiliformis grandis<\/em>. Closer examination shines a light on P. magnastoma\u2019s stand out feature. Its rather large oral groove is equal in size to that of <em>Porrectofrontus mechadeus<\/em> and only smaller than that of<em> Aspericardis lehmeri<\/em> among other Toxodentidae. <em>P. magnastoma<\/em> has been observed in biomes similar to those <em>P. mechadeus<\/em> is found in, namely plastic bags containing large and\/or heavy produce. Perhaps its smaller external morphology makes it safer from predation. The bags it has been seen attached to are often a mix of plastic mesh and plastic sheet. It is unclear whether <em>P. magnastoma<\/em> requires this mixed biome to remain healthy. They are commonly white but pale blue specimens have been located, and a pale yellow specimen was observed in Turkey, a rare sighting for the region. Discovered by field researcher C. Reeves, and described by occlupanologist C. Huning of DWORC.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Palpatophora magnastoma &#8220;Big-mouth palp-bearer&#8221; Kingdom Microsynthera Phylum Plasticae Class Occlupanida Order Orthogonidectes Family Toxodentidae Genus Palpatophora Species magnastoma External morphology Lateral palps. Size 21.5 mm x 26 mm At first glance P. magnastoma could be one of a few very common occlupanid species: P. glyphodorsalis, P. utiliformis, or P. utiliformis grandis. Closer examination shines a [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":2064,"parent":749,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":[],"aioseo_notices":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/pages\/2057"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fcomments&post=2057"}],"version-history":[{"count":8,"href":"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/pages\/2057\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":3122,"href":"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/pages\/2057\/revisions\/3122"}],"up":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/pages\/749"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/media\/2064"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"http:\/\/www.horg.com\/horg\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fmedia&parent=2057"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}